Sentencas: The electromotive force (e.m.f) is calculated for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) based on doped ceria electrolytes using biomass-produced gases (BPG, 14.7% CO, 14.2% CO2, 15.3% H-2, 4.2% CH4, and 51% N-2) as fuels and air as oxidant.
Titulo: Low-temperature SOFCs using biomass-produced gases as fuels

Sentencas: It reveals that the BPG derived e.m.f. is very close to hydrogen when doped ceria is used as the electrolyte.
Titulo: Low-temperature SOFCs using biomass-produced gases as fuels

Sentencas: A 35-mum-thick samaria-doped ceria based single cell was tested between 450 and 650degreesC using BPG as fuel.
Titulo: Low-temperature SOFCs using biomass-produced gases as fuels

Sentencas: Maximum power density of about 700 mW cm(-2) was achieved at 650degreesC. The open-circuit voltage at 450degreesC was 0.96 V, close to the calculated value.
Titulo: Low-temperature SOFCs using biomass-produced gases as fuels

Sentencas: However, the cell power density using BPG as fuel was relatively lower than that using humidified hydrogen (3% H2O), and close to that using humidified methane (3% H2O).
Titulo: Low-temperature SOFCs using biomass-produced gases as fuels

Sentencas: Impedance measurements indicate that the relatively lower power output may be attributed to the high anode-electrolyte interfacial polarization resistance when BPG is used as fuel.
Titulo: Low-temperature SOFCs using biomass-produced gases as fuels
